OL,6,FBut Lucy said she is more scared for
OL,7,Fher son who attends a Jewish school
OL,8,Fthat is now heavily guarded by
OL,9,Fsecurity.
OL,11,F"There is a strong police presence
OL,12,Foutside every single day and it just
OL,13,Fbreaks my heart. I feel like i'm
OL,14,Fputting him in harms way," she said.
OL,16,F"He doesn't understand, thankfully,
OL,17,Fbut he did ask me the other day why
OL,18,Fthe police were there, I didn't know
OL,19,Fwhat to say.
